question:
Consider the following method that takes a `Car` object as a parameter. What will be the output of the program?

```java
class Car {
    String color;
    Car(String color) { this.color = color; }
}

public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Car myCar = new Car("Red");
        changeColor(myCar);
        System.out.println(myCar.color);
    }

    public static void changeColor(Car car) {
        car.color = "Blue";
    }
}
```

